      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) is directly relevant to the clinical decision context. Secondary QoIs (shear stress distribution, exposure time) are mechanistically linked to erythrocyte damage and support identification of worst-case operating conditions."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Achieved level must meet or exceed required level for MRL 2.",
      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry, which is a recognized surrogate for Class II CPB devices. Operating conditions in validation experiments bracket the CPB clinical operating envelope. Validation relevance is judged adequate for MRL 2."
    },
    {
